    "Secure airway under controlled conditions": "Highly reasonable given the risk of airway compromise from a bleeding, friable mass.",
    "Excisional/wide incisional biopsy": "Essential; however, must be done with caution for hemorrhage.",
    "Immunohistochemical staining": "Reasonable; standard for undifferentiated tumors.",
    "Molecular testing": "Reasonable; aids in diagnosis and potential targeted therapy.",
    "MRI of the neck": "Reasonable; superior to CT for soft tissue definition and vascular anatomy.",
    "Systemic staging": "Reasonable; indicated if malignancy is confirmed."
